William Woodruff
Professor John Beckett writes:
Your obituary of William Woodruff (deceased on September 25) states that "in 1946 he had resumed his studies in economic history at Oxford, and in 1950 became a member of Houblon-Norma research, while he was doing a BSc, an MA, and a PhD."
